---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
import HtmlTool from '../components/HtmlTool.tsx';
import LandingLinks from '../components/LandingLinks.astro';
---

<ToolPage
  title="HTML Viewer & Formatter — Render HTML Online Free"
  description="Paste HTML to preview it rendered in a safe sandbox, or beautify messy markup instantly. Free online HTML viewer and formatter, runs in your browser."
  h1="HTML Viewer & Formatter"
  intro="Paste HTML on the left to see it rendered safely on the right, or switch to Format to beautify messy markup. Rendering happens in a sandboxed iframe — scripts never run."
  path="/html"
  faq={[
    {
      q: 'Will JavaScript in my HTML run?',
      a: 'No. Scripts are removed and the sandbox blocks execution, by design.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Can I beautify minified HTML?',
      a: 'Yes — switch to the Format tab to re-indent and wrap minified or messy markup.',
    },
    {
      q: 'Will external stylesheets or interactive widgets work?',
      a: 'The preview is intended for static markup. Scripts are blocked, and external resources or browser-dependent widgets may not match a production page.',
    },
  ]}
>
  <HtmlTool client:only="react" />

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <h2 class="mt-8 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Preview and format HTML online</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      This tool does two things: it <strong>renders</strong> your HTML so you can see the result, and
      it <strong>formats</strong> (beautifies) messy markup with proper indentation. Great for quickly
      checking a snippet, cleaning up copied code, or learning how a layout behaves.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Is it safe?</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Yes. Pasted HTML is sanitized (scripts and event handlers are stripped) and then rendered inside
      a sandboxed iframe with scripts disabled — so nothing malicious can run against your browser or
      this page.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">How the two modes differ</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      <strong>Preview</strong> answers “what does this static markup render?” while
      <strong>Format</strong> answers “how is this document nested?” Preview sanitizes the input and
      displays it in an isolated frame. Format uses a code formatter to add consistent indentation
      and line breaks. Formatting improves readability; it is not an HTML validator and does not fix
      every semantic or accessibility problem.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Useful checks before publishing HTML</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
      <li>Confirm that opening and closing tags are nested where you expect.</li>
      <li>Check headings in a logical order and add useful alternative text to images.</li>
      <li>Test links, forms, responsive CSS and JavaScript in the real target environment.</li>
      <li>Never treat a sandboxed preview as proof that untrusted HTML is safe to publish elsewhere.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Why the preview may differ from your website</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      A pasted fragment does not automatically include your site’s stylesheets, fonts, scripts or
      surrounding layout. Interactive components are intentionally disabled. For an accurate final
      check, copy the cleaned markup back into the project and test it with the same CSS and assets
      the production page uses.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-6 text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Will JavaScript in my HTML run?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">No. Scripts are removed and the sandbox blocks execution, by design.</p>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Can I beautify minified HTML?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      Yes — switch to the <strong>Format</strong> tab to re-indent and wrap minified or messy markup.
    </p>
    <h3 class="mt-4 font-semibold text-slate-800">Will external stylesheets or interactive widgets work?</h3>
    <p class="mt-1">
      The preview is intended for static markup. Scripts are blocked, and external resources or
      browser-dependent widgets may not match a production page.
    </p>

    <LandingLinks group="html" heading="More HTML tools" />
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>
